You are missing `#container` on the element:

    &lt;a class=&quot;link&quot; [routerLink]=&quot;[&#39;/home&#39;]&quot; routerLinkActive=&quot;active&quot; #container&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;

`#container` references the element with `@ViewChild()`. The `@ViewChild()` decorator queries for the element using the selector which is `container` in your case.

**Edit for the updated question:**

For getting the children elements use `ElementRef&lt;HTMLElement&gt;;`:

    @ViewChild(&#39;container&#39;, { static: true }) container: ElementRef&lt;HTMLElement&gt;;

